<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 12:50AM EDT  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG...
Widespread fog with visibilities of 1 to 2 miles has developed,
with patchy dense fog with visibilities 1/4 mile or less.
Visibilities will be improving by 300 AM EDT as a weak cold front
moves through the region. If you are driving overnight be prepared
for varying visibilities, slow down, and increase distance to the
vehicle in front. Use low beams.</description>
